{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idef84146c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2422"},"text":"§ 2422.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Content of application","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An application for a certificate recognizing plant variety rights shall contain:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef84146d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The name of the variety except that a temporary designation will suffice until the certificate is to be issued. The variety shall be named in accordance with regulations issued by the Secretary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef84146e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A description of the variety setting forth its distinctiveness, uniformity, and stability and a description of the genealogy and breeding procedure, when known. The Secretary may require amplification, including the submission of adequate photographs or drawings or plant specimens, if the description is not adequate or as complete as is reasonably possible, and submission of records or proof of ownership or of allegations made in the application. An applicant may add to or correct the description at any time, before the certificate is issued, upon a showing acceptable to the Secretary that the revised description is retroactively accurate. Courts shall protect others from any injustice which would result. The Secretary may accept rec­ords of the breeder and of any official seed certifying agency in this country as evidence of stability where applicable.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef84146f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A statement of the basis of the claim of the applicant that the variety is new.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef841470-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A declaration that a viable sample of basic seed (including any propagating material) necessary for propagation of the variety will be deposited and replenished periodically in a public repository in accordance with regulations to be established hereunder.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef841471-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2422/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A statement of the basis of applicant’s ownership.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idef841472-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/577/tII/s52"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–577, title II, § 52","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-24"},"text":"Dec. 24, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1548"},"text":"84 Stat. 1548","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/574/s11"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–574, § 11","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3350"},"text":"94 Stat. 3350","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3139"},"text":"108 Stat. 3139","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idef841473-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idef841474-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idef841475-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “The variety shall be named in accordance with regulations issued by the Secretary.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4(2)","children":[],"tail":", in first sentence substituted “distinctiveness, uniformity, and stability” for “novelty”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4(4)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3). Former par. (3) redesignated (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4(3)","children":[],"tail":", (5), redesignated par. (3) as (4) and inserted “(including any propagating material)” after “basic seed”. Former par. (4) redesignated (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s4/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349, § 4(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (4) as (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/574"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–574","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions relating to adding of declaration by amendment."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idef841476-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idef841477-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–349","children":[],"tail":" effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1994","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/349/s15"},"text":"section 15 of Pub. L. 103–349","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2401"},"text":"section 2401 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
